<br>
She had taken a single white rose with her as she walked towards the Tanias River which was the closest to Scynthia. She smiled looking over the large waters slightly catching a glimpse of Yakut's tribe on the other side of the waters.<br>
<br>
She then placed her kiss upon the petals of the rose and smiled making her wish.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hera, although I have no patron Goddess, and I do not worship the Olympian Gods, I am a fellow Scynthian sister of you, and this being your festival, I ask for your guidance. I am having troubles in finding a common ground between my warrior ways as well as those of my husband. Please assist me with guidance Hera.&quot;<br>
<br>
She kissed the rose once more before setting it into the waters and watching it flow downstream. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen of the Gods</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#993300>(6/21/01 5:50:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=160.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qherarpg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summer Solstice</span><hr size=1> ~*~ Before a shimmering light flashed and then softly dissappeared to the sound of the cry of peacocks.  There in it's stead stood Hera, Queen of the Gods.  She smiled softly at Alysia. ~*~<br>
